author: TEDx Talks
description:
In this eye-opening TEDx talk, Jean-Sébastien Busque shares an unexpected social experiment that began with a single bathroom visit. After transitioning and experiencing public restrooms from both perspectives, he uncovered striking differences in behavior, unwritten rules, and social dynamics between men's and women's spaces.

If you'd like to contact Jean-Sebastien Busque, please visit www.jsbusque.com After 20+ years in the corporate world, Jean-Sébastien Busque reinvented his life when grief, burnout, and a gender transition made it impossible to keep pretending. Now, he is a speaker, author of "My Apple Pie of Happiness" and founder of Cohérence conseil, guiding organizations and individuals from chaos to clarity with fearless authenticity! 

This talk was given at a TEDx event using the TED conference format but independently organized by a local community. Learn more at https://www.ted.com/tedx
title: What I learned about gender norms from public restrooms | Jean-Sébastien Busque | TEDxFullerton
